iati-activity.description:
Aim: encourage students to actively and responsibly take on the role of promoters of sustainable positive changes within the community they belong to

Specific objectives:
-	Acknowledge and encourage voluntarism as a tool of non-formal education and stimulate civic participation of 50 students;
-	Develop the institutional capacity of 3 students non-governmental structures for an efficient management of activities;
-	Inform at least 400 students on the opportunities provided by the participation in voluntary activities.

The goal of the project is to make rural communities in Southern Georgia resilient to natural disasters caused by climate changes and to reduce the negative impact these disasters impose on the human and economic development of these communities.

Expected outcomes and outputs:
1)	 The concept of community based disaster risk reduction is promoted in Georgia.
1.1. The team of Caritas Georgia (min. 5 persons) has been trained in the basic conceptions and methods of community based disaster risk reduction;
1.2. A set of written materials and tools has been published in Georgian language;
1.3. A final one-day conference presenting the implementation and the results of the project has been organized.

2) The community of Tsintskaro and its members are prepared to cope with situations of natural disasters.
2.1. A local initiative group with 10 members, having knowledge and capacities in disaster risk reduction established in Tsintskaro.
2.2.	A risk assessment has been conducted by the local initiative group and the community facilitator of Caritas Georgia providing information about hazards, vulnerabilities and capacities of the community and proposing measures to reduce the risk;
2.3.	An action plan describing the main activities that will be implemented in the local community of Tsintskaro has been developed by the local initiative group;
2.4	A disaster preparedness program has been implemented in the village Tsintskaro.

3)The village of Tsintskaro has a concrete plan to mitigate the impact of annual spring floods;
3.1. A plan proposing measures to mitigate the impact of floods in the local community of Tsintskaro has been elaborated;
3.2. At least two non-structural measures to mitigate the impact of floods have been implemented by the initiative group in collaboration with the population and the local authorities.
